ğŸ¯ How It Works:
Screen Lock Authentication:
User enables "Device Screen Lock" in account settings
System checks if device has a screen lock configured
When authenticating, user is prompted with device's native unlock screen
Supports PIN, pattern, password, fingerprint, face recognition, etc.
Passkey Authentication:
User enables "Passkey" in account settings
System prompts user to create a secure passkey (min 6 chars)
Passkey is hashed with SHA-256 and stored securely
When authenticating, user enters their passkey
System verifies the hash and grants access
